HEADWORD: Birrus
<hw>Bir"rus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL., fr. L.
<ets>birrus</ets> a kind of cloak. See <er>Berretta</er>.]</ety> <def>A
coarse kind of thick woolen cloth, worn by the poor in the Middle Ages;
also, a woolen cap or hood worn over the shoulders or over the
head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

